cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a language model based on recurrent neural networks. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses improving the expressive power of the language model. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper proposes a method for improving language modeling, which is a key task in natural language processing. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the proposed method involves using multiple layers of a recurrent neural network. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions two application tasks, one of which is headline generation, which could be related to computer vision and image captioning.
